.TH CSVVIEW 1 "2026-03-21" "csvview 15" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
csvview \- fast terminal CSV viewer and editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B csvview
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIfile\fR
.br
.B csvview
.BR \-\-cat
[\fB\-\-column=\fINAME\fR] [\fB\-\-output=\fIFILE\fR] \fIfile1\fR \fIfile2\fR ...
.br
.B csvview
.BR \-\-split
.B \-\-by=\fICOLUMN\fR
[\fB\-\-output\-dir=\fIDIR\fR] [\fB\-\-drop\-col\fR] \fIfile\fR
.br
.B csvview
.BR \-\-dedup
[\fB\-\-by=\fIcol1,col2\fR] [\fB\-\-keep=\fIfirst\fR|\fIlast\fR] [\fB\-\-output=\fIFILE\fR] \fIfile\fR
.br
.B csvview
(no arguments \(em opens recent file picker)
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B csvview
is a terminal-based CSV viewer and editor built with ncurses.
It supports filtering, sorting, pivot tables, graphs, computed columns,
column statistics, colour themes, and more \(em with no external dependencies
beyond ncurses.
Handles files up to 50 million rows using
.BR mmap (2)
and parallel processing (up to 8 threads).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-sep= CHAR
Use \fICHAR\fR as the field delimiter. Examples: \fB\-\-sep=\\t\fR (TSV),
\fB\-\-sep=;\fR, \fB\-\-sep=|\fR.
File extension is auto-detected: \fI.csv\fR\(->comma, \fI.tsv\fR\(->tab, \fI.psv\fR\(->pipe.
.TP
.BI \-\-theme= NAME
Start with the named colour theme. Available themes:
.BR dark ", " light ", " tokyonight ", " nord ", " catppuccin .
The choice is saved to \fI~/.config/csvview/config\fR and remembered for
future sessions.
.TP
.B \-\-cat
Concatenate multiple CSV files into one, adding a column with the source filename.
.TP
.BI \-\-column= NAME
Column name for the source filename in \fB\-\-cat\fR mode (default: \fIsource_file\fR).
.TP
.BI \-\-output= FILE
Output filename for \fB\-\-cat\fR mode (default: \fImerged_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.csv\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-dedup
Remove duplicate rows from a CSV file.
By default keeps the first occurrence of each duplicate.
.TP
.BI \-\-keep= first | last
Which occurrence to keep when deduplicating (default: \fBfirst\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-split
Split a CSV file into multiple files, one per unique value of a column.
.TP
.BI \-\-by= COLUMN
Column to split by (required with \fB\-\-split\fR).
.TP
.BI \-\-output\-dir= DIR
Directory for split output files (created if needed).
.TP
.B \-\-drop\-col
Remove the split column from all output files.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-? ", " \-\-help ", " /h
Show help and exit.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.SS Main view
.TP
.B Arrows / hjkl
Move cursor
.TP
.B PageUp / PageDown
Scroll one page
.TP
.B Home / End
First / last visible row
.TP
.B /
Start simple search
.TP
.B n / N
Next / previous search result
.TP
.B f
Quick filter (Tab autocompletes column names)
.TP
.B Shift+F
Advanced filter (Tab autocompletes column names)
.TP
.B Enter
Edit current cell
.TP
.B u
Undo last cell edit (up to 20 steps)
.TP
.B s
Save file
.TP
.B t
Column settings (type, format, width, hide/show)
.TP
.B w / W
Increase / decrease column width
.TP
.B A
Auto-fit current column width
.TP
.B [ / ]
Sort ascending / descending by current column
.TP
.B r / R
Reset sorting
.TP
.B Ctrl+R
Reload file (keeps filters and sort)
.TP
.B Ctrl+G
Go to row by number (prompts)
.TP
.B z
Freeze / unfreeze columns up to current
.TP
.B X
Hide / show current column (in column settings)
.TP
.B d / D
Column statistics (sum, mean, median, histogram \(em numeric and date)
.TP
.B p / P
Pivot table (\fBp\fR reuses saved settings, \fBP\fR always opens settings window)
.TP
.B g / G
Graph for current column (line / bar / dot)
.TP
.B q / Esc
Quit
.TP
.B ?
Show help
.SS Command mode (press \fB:\fR)
.TP
.BI : N
Go to row N (1-based). Example: \fB:1000\fR
.TP
.BI :+ N " / " :- N
Relative jump: N rows down / up from the current row.
Pairs with \fB:rn\fR relative line numbers to count the offset visually.
.TP
.BI :e " [file]"
Export current view (with active filter / sort) to CSV.
Default filename: \fIfiltered.csv\fR / \fIsorted.csv\fR / \fItable.csv\fR.
.TP
.BI :dr " N"
Delete row N (visible 1-based row number).
.TP
.BI :cr " name"
Rename current column.
.TP
.BI :cal " [name]"
Add column to the left of current column.
.TP
.BI :car " [name]"
Add column to the right of current column.
.TP
.BI :cf " formula"
Fill / compute column by formula (see
.B COMPUTED COLUMNS
below).
.TP
.BI :cd " name"
Delete column (cursor must be on that column).
.TP
.BI :cs " [file]"
Export current column to CSV.
.TP
.BI :fz " N"
Freeze first N columns (\fB:fz 0\fR unfreezes all).
.TP
.BI :dedup " [col1,col2] [--keep=last]"
Hide duplicate rows, keeping only unique combinations of the specified columns
(or all columns if none given).
The result is applied as a filter; use \fB:e\fR to export deduplicated data.
\fB\-\-keep=last\fR retains the last occurrence instead of the first.
.TP
.B :fs
Save current filter to \fIfile.csvf\fR.
.TP
.B :fl
Open saved filters list.
.TP
.B :fq
Quick filter: current column = current cell value (AND).
.TP
.B :fqn
Quick filter: current column != current cell value (AND).
.TP
.B :fqo
Quick filter: current column = current cell value (OR).
.TP
.B :fqu
Reset filter and apply: current column = current cell value.
.TP
.B :rn
Toggle relative line numbers (shows distance from cursor row instead of
absolute row number). The current row always shows its absolute number.
.TP
.BI :theme " [name]"
Switch colour theme. Without an argument, lists available themes and the
currently active one. The selection is saved to \fI~/.config/csvview/config\fR.
.TP
.B :open
Close current file and reopen the recent-file picker.
.SS Graph commands (press \fB:\fR inside graph view)
.TP
.BI :gt " type"
Graph type: \fBbar\fR, \fBline\fR, or \fBdot\fR.
.TP
.BI :gt " scale"
Y-axis scale: \fBlog\fR or \fBlin\fR.
.TP
.BI :gc " colour"
Graph colour: \fBred\fR, \fBgreen\fR, \fBblue\fR, \fByellow\fR, \fBcyan\fR, \fBmagenta\fR, \fBwhite\fR.
.TP
.BI :gy " scale"
Y-axis scale: \fBlog\fR or \fBlinear\fR.
.TP
.BI :ga " on\fR|\fBoff"
Anomaly highlighting (values more than 3\(*s from the mean).
.TP
.BI :gx " column\fR|\fBoff"
Use a date column as the X axis (Tab autocompletes column name).
\fB:gx off\fR resets to row numbers.
.TP
.BI :gp " on\fR|\fBoff"
Show / hide cursor on data points.
.SH FILTER SYNTAX
Filters support: \fB= != > >= < <=\fR, \fBAND\fR, \fBOR\fR, \fB!\fR (NOT).
.PP
Examples:
.RS
total > 500
.br
total >= 100 AND status = paid
.br
date >= 2026-01
.br
date >= 2025-Q1 AND date <= 2025-Q3
.br
! cohort = 2016-04
.RE
.PP
Date matching:
.RS
\fB= 2026-01\fR \(em all rows in January 2026
.br
\fB<= 2025-08\fR \(em up to and including August 2025
.br
\fB>= 2025-Q2\fR \(em Q2 2025 and later (quarter format \fBYYYY-Qn\fR)
.RE
.SH COMPUTED COLUMNS
Activated with \fB:cf <expression>\fR on the current column.
.PP
Operators: \fB+ \- * / ( )\fR, unary \fB\-\fR
.br
Comparisons (inside \fBif()\fR): \fB= != < <= > >=\fR
.br
Functions: \fBround\fR, \fBabs\fR, \fBfloor\fR, \fBceil\fR, \fBmod\fR, \fBpow\fR, \fBif\fR, \fBempty\fR
.br
Aggregates (filtered rows): \fBcol_sum\fR, \fBcol_avg\fR, \fBcol_min\fR, \fBcol_max\fR,
\fBcol_count\fR, \fBcol_median\fR, \fBcol_percentile\fR, \fBcol_stddev\fR, \fBcol_var\fR,
\fBcol_rank\fR, \fBcol_pct\fR
.br
Aggregates (whole file): same names with \fB_all\fR suffix
(e.g.\& \fBcol_sum_all\fR, \fBcol_rank_all\fR)
.PP
Examples:
.RS
:cf price * qty
.br
:cf round((revenue - cost) / revenue * 100, 2)
.br
:cf if(qty > 0, revenue / qty, 0)
.br
:cf col_pct(revenue)
.br
:cf col_rank_all(score)
.RE
.SH COLOUR THEMES
Five built-in themes selectable with \fB:theme\fR or \fB\-\-theme\fR:
.TP
.B dark
Default dark theme.
.TP
.B light
Light theme: white background, black text, yellow highlights, blue cursor.
.TP
.B tokyonight
Tokyo Night \(em dark blue background, blue cursor, yellow accent.
.TP
.B nord
Nord \(em cold grey-blue background, Frost blue cursor, Aurora yellow accent.
.TP
.B catppuccin
Catppuccin Mocha \(em dark background, mauve cursor, peach accent.
.PP
Falls back to 8 basic colours on terminals with fewer than 256 colours.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.csvview_history
Recent files list (max 20 entries).
Opened automatically when csvview is run with no arguments or via \fB:open\fR.
.TP
.I ~/.config/csvview/config
User configuration. Currently stores \fBtheme=\fIname\fR.
Respects \fB$XDG_CONFIG_HOME\fR if set.
.TP
.I file.csvf
Per-file settings: column types, formats, widths, hidden columns,
freeze count, saved filters.
.TP
.I file.pivot
Saved pivot table settings for the file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Open a CSV file:
.B csvview data.csv
.TP
Open with Tokyo Night theme:
.B csvview \-\-theme=tokyonight data.csv
.TP
Open a TSV file:
.B csvview data.tsv
.TP
Open with semicolon delimiter:
.B csvview \-\-sep=; data.csv
.TP
Jump to row 5000 then 200 rows further down:
.B :5000
then
.B :+200
.TP
Merge files with source column:
.B csvview \-\-cat \-\-column=source \-\-output=merged.csv jan.csv feb.csv mar.csv
.TP
Split by region column:
.B csvview \-\-split \-\-by=region \-\-output\-dir=splits data.csv
.TP
Remove fully duplicate rows:
.B csvview \-\-dedup data.csv
.TP
Deduplicate by email column, keep last occurrence:
.B csvview \-\-dedup \-\-by=email \-\-keep=last \-\-output=clean.csv data.csv
.TP
Deduplicate interactively by two columns:
.B :dedup country,city
.TP
Deduplicate interactively, keep last:
.B :dedup id \-\-keep=last
